      "content": "that's pretty intense. i like the idea of the trauma being a physical presence. i'm trying to figure out how to make the 'monsters' or the 'evil' feel specific to the neighborhood though. like, instead of just generic ghosts, can you suggest some ways the actual reputation or the 'vibe' of the people living there could dictate what the creatures look like or how they behave? i want the horror to feel like it's born out of the specific identity of the area so it doesn't feel like a generic ghost story.",
